cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.SD

The paper proposes an autonomous learning algorithm for generating deep convolutional neural network (DCNN) architectures for image classification. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also involves the use of evolutionary operations for evolving a population of DCNN architectures, which falls under the sub-categories of cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). Additionally, the paper involves the use of activation and drop out, which are techniques used in neural networks, falling under the sub-category of cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). Finally, the paper involves the use of refined evolutionary operations, which falls under the sub-category of cs.SD (Software Engineering).
